block content
	section.pageContent
		h1.pageHeading About
		div.contentBody
			p.primaryText_center Parents may want to know what their children are reading.  Victims of abuse may not want to read about abuse for entertainment.  There are plenty of reasons to know the content of what you are reading.
			p.primaryText_center We are trying to create a way for people to be informed about what's in their books.
			p Categories include: Substances, Sex, Violence, Language, Abuse, Hate, Immorality, Occult.
				pre
					| 0 - No appearance
					| 1 - Some reference or inuendo involving
					| 2 - references to or second-hand descriptions of
					| 3 - descriptions or brief scenes involving
					| 4 - scenes or themes with this as a major element
					| 5 - majority content of book 

		h1.pageHeading FAQs
		div.contentBody
			h2 Why don't you have age ratings?
			p We want to provide information regarding comment so that you can decide what is appropriate and what is not.  Also, most books are already categorized as young adult, teen, or children's.

			h2 "Immorality" as a category? "Occult"?  Isn't this a little subjective?
			p Yes.  But this is why there is a place to add comments next to your rating to clarify what you mean.

